question: Which country houses "Lake Saimaa"?
explanation: Lake Saimaa is a lake located in southeastern Finland. This lake is the largest lake in Finland and the fourth-largest natural freshwater lake in Europe. Vuoksi River and Saimaa Canal from the primary outflows of the Lake Saimaa. This lake forms the habitat of an endangered freshwater seal, the Saimaa Ringed Seal, which lives only at Saimaa.
